#. <section class="sutta" id="sn56.36"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn56.36:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.36:0.2"
msgid "4. Sīsapāvanavagga"
msgstr "4. In a Rosewood Forest"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn56.36:0.3"
msgid "36. Pāṇasutta"
msgstr "36. Living Creatures"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.36:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso yaṃ imasmiṃ jambudīpe tiṇakaṭṭhasākhāpalāsaṃ "
"tacchetvā ekajjhaṃ saṃhareyya;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose a person was to strip all the grass, sticks, branches, and leaves in "
"India, gather them together into one pile,"

msgctxt "sn56.36:1.2"
msgid "ekajjhaṃ saṃharitvā sūlaṃ kareyya."
msgstr "and make them into stakes."

msgctxt "sn56.36:1.3"
msgid ""
"Sūlaṃ karitvā ye mahāsamudde mahantakā pāṇā te mahantakesu sūlesu āvuneyya, "
"ye mahāsamudde majjhimakā pāṇā te majjhimakesu sūlesu āvuneyya, ye "
"mahāsamudde sukhumakā pāṇā te sukhumakesu sūlesu āvuneyya."
msgstr ""
"Then they’d impale the large creatures in the ocean on large stakes; the "
"medium-sized creatures on medium-sized stakes; and the small creatures on "
"small stakes."

msgctxt "sn56.36:1.4"
msgid "Apariyādinnā ca, bhikkhave, mahāsamudde oḷārikā pāṇā assu."
msgstr "They wouldn’t run out of sizable creatures in the ocean before"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.442"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.36:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha imasmiṃ jambudīpe tiṇakaṭṭhasākhāpalāsaṃ parikkhayaṃ pariyādānaṃ "
"gaccheyya."
msgstr "using up all the grass, sticks, branches, and leaves in India."

msgctxt "sn56.36:2.2"
msgid ""
"Ito bahutarā kho, bhikkhave, mahāsamudde sukhumakā pāṇā, ye na sukarā sūlesu "
"āvunituṃ."
msgstr ""
"There are far more small creatures in the ocean than this, so it wouldn’t be "
"feasible to impale them on stakes."

msgctxt "sn56.36:2.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn56.36:2.4"
msgid "Sukhumattā, bhikkhave, attabhāvassa."
msgstr "Because of the small size of those life-forms."

msgctxt "sn56.36:2.5"
msgid "Evaṃ mahā kho, bhikkhave, apāyo."
msgstr "That’s how big the plane of loss is."

msgctxt "sn56.36:2.6"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ mahantasmā kho, bhikkhave, apāyasmā parimutto diṭṭhisampanno puggalo ‘"
"idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī "
"paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"A person accomplished in view, exempt from that vast plane of loss, truly "
"understands: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This "
"is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the "
"cessation of suffering’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.36:3.1"
msgid ""
"Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yogo karaṇīyo … pe … ‘ayaṃ "
"dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti."
msgstr "That’s why you should practice meditation …”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.36:3.2"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
